column33:
The problem with all the protein enhanced food items that I have generally come across is that they are priced very high with very little differentiation (in terms of nutrition) from the original product. 'Protein rich'. 'high fiber', 'healthy', are just marketing claims. 
I'm spending almost Rs 3.5 / gm protein on whey supplement; if a roti provides me the same value, I'll be more than happy to make that purchase.
